      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RESURRECTED (1) did well last start when he did his best work late but found one better over 1350m at Doomben, beaten only 1.5 lengths. Andrew Mallyon gets the best out of this five-year-old and reunites. Beautifully placed and is sure to take a ton of beating. KAIROS LOUIE (2) couldn't quite go on with the job when well found at Eagle Farm off his dominant first-up win. Tackling a more suitable race this time so he is a major player. DO IT FOR YOU (6) has returned in terrific order this campaign, as he shoots for the hat-trick. Stiffer opposition this time but he can step up to the mark. LADY ALABAMA (4) progressed nicely last time out to finish within a length of the winner in second at Grafton. Worth noting Bella Youngberry goes aboard and has partnered in all three of her wins. Finds a nice race and can keep improving.",
